Cicero was now in his 27th year ¹. Prior to Sulla’s dictator- ship he had not practised in the law-courts : for indeed there were no law-courts to practise in 2. But his spare figure might have been seen daily in the Forum with long thin neck outstretched, eager to catch the tones of the popular orators as they thundered from the rostra ³. And all the time he had been assiduously practising rhetoric, chiefly under Greek masterS, and studying philosophy, logie, and civil law, so that when the courts had been re-established, and he at length appeared in the Forum in his 26th year (Rc. 81), it was not to learn by experience like others, but to exercise the art of which he was already a master ⁴.
